onsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530314\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 15, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nlv1665702678531.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nlv1665702678531.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nlv1665702678531.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"nlv1665702678531\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__flow_of_calls_to_the_smtp_security_driver_api_432733\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Calls to an SMTP security driver are issued by operations on the Uniface UPOPMAIL component. These have an equivalent 3GL implementation which handles the actual call.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__p_d132479e1_d132480e1_d132481e1\">An instance of the UPOPMAIL component can be used to open a connection and the close it, and then open a connection to another server and close it. The security context is maintained over connections so the driver receives only one call for <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_DRVINFO</code>. This means that when a connection is closed, the driver should return to exactly the same state it was in after the initial <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_DRVINFO</code> call. In this way, each new connection is created from the same starting point.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__p_d132482e1_d132483e1_d132484e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_RTINFO</code> call provides information about the current or previous connection. When a connection is being made, the driver is marked as in use depending on the <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_VERIFY</code> call result. Once the driver is in use, it can receive <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_RTINFO</code> calls.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__p_d132485e1_d132486e1_d132487e1\">API calls are typically issued in the following order.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47297e1_d47298e1_d47299e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">…</code> function may be called a number of times\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47300e1_d47301e1_d47302e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">[]</code> function called if the implementation supports it\n </li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Flow of API Calls to the SMTP Security Driver</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__1\">\n Calling Operation\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__2\">\n API Function Code\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__1 nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__2\">\n                     When opening a connection: \n                  </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">SetSecurity</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_DRVINFO</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">LogonSMTP</code> (may be called\n                     implicitly by <code class=\"ph codeph\">SendMail</code>) </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_VERIFY</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">LogonSMTP</code> (may be called\n                     implicitly by <code class=\"ph codeph\">SendMail</code>) </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__2\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_OPENMSG</code><code class=\"ph codeph\">…</code></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__1 nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__2\">\n                     During or after a connection: \n                  </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">GetSecurity</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__2\">[<code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_RTINFO</code>] </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__1 nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__2\">When closing the connection, if\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_OPENMSG</code> succeeded: </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">LogoffSMTP</code> (may be called\n                     implicitly by <code class=\"ph codeph\">SendMail</code>) </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__2\">[<code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_CLOSEMSG</code>…] </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__1 nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__2\">\n                     When deleting the instance: \n                  </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">upopmail_cleanup</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15764e1_d15765e1_d15766e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_CLOSE</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__topic_d94142e1_d94143e1_d94144e1_d94145e1_d94146e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d912874e259\">\n                       \n Interactions Between UPOPMAIL and Security API Functions\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__p_d132491e1_d132492e1_d132493e1\">The operations of the UPOPMAIL service are called using its 4GL interface. The 3GL implementations of these operations handle all TCP communication and are the callers of the generic API.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__p_d132494e1_d132495e1_d132496e1\">The following tables show the actions and interactions between the UPOPMAIL and security driver API layers during calls to the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">SetSecurity</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">LogonSMTP</span> operations. <code class=\"ph codeph\">MyModule</code> is an SMTP security driver implementation. It specifies its own functionality and prepares messages.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15767e1_d15768e1_d15769e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">During the SetSecurity Operation</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15767e1_d15768e1_d15769e1__entry__1\">\n Layer\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15767e1_d15768e1_d15769e1__entry__2\">\n Call and Actions\n </th>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15767e1_d15768e1_d15769e1__entry__3\">\n UPOPMAIL Service\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15767e1_d15768e1_d15769e1__entry__1 nlv1665702678531__table_d15767e1_d15768e1_d15769e1__entry__3\">\n 4GL UPOPMAIL\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15767e1_d15768e1_d15769e1__entry__2 nlv1665702678531__table_d15767e1_d15768e1_d15769e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">activate UPOPINSTANCE.SetSecurity(\"SMTP=MyModule\", \"user=andy;pass=pandy\")</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15767e1_d15768e1_d15769e1__entry__1 nlv1665702678531__table_d15767e1_d15768e1_d15769e1__entry__3\">\n 3GL UPOPMAIL\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15767e1_d15768e1_d15769e1__entry__2 nlv1665702678531__table_d15767e1_d15768e1_d15769e1__entry__3\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">SetSecurity</code> (3GL\n                        implementation) </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15767e1_d15768e1_d15769e1__entry__1 nlv1665702678531__table_d15767e1_d15768e1_d15769e1__entry__3\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15767e1_d15768e1_d15769e1__entry__2 nlv1665702678531__table_d15767e1_d15768e1_d15769e1__entry__3\">\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47303e1_d47304e1_d47305e1\">Create API structure Initialise structure with function address of <code class=\"ph codeph\">MyModule</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47306e1_d47307e1_d47308e1\">Initialize structure with <code class=\"ph codeph\">\"user=andy;pass=pandy\"</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47309e1_d47310e1_d47311e1\">Initialize structure with <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_DRVINFO</code> function code\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47312e1_d47313e1_d47314e1\">Set <code class=\"ph codeph\">USE</code> flag to <code class=\"ph codeph\">Mandatory</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47315e1_d47316e1_d47317e1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Call <code class=\"ph codeph\">MyModule</code>with structure parameter</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15770e1_d15771e1_d15772e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15770e1_d15771e1_d15772e1__entry__1\">\n Security Driver\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15770e1_d15771e1_d15772e1__entry__1\">\n 3GL MyModule\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15770e1_d15771e1_d15772e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_DRVINFO</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15770e1_d15771e1_d15772e1__entry__1\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15770e1_d15771e1_d15772e1__entry__1\">\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47318e1_d47319e1_d47320e1\">Set bit flag to show <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_OPENMSG</code> is supported\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47321e1_d47322e1_d47323e1\">Return success\n </li>\n</ol>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15773e1_d15774e1_d15775e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 3. </span><span class=\"title\">During the LogonSMTP Operation</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15773e1_d15774e1_d15775e1__entry__1\">\n Layer\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15773e1_d15774e1_d15775e1__entry__2\">\n Call and Actions\n </th>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15773e1_d15774e1_d15775e1__entry__3\">\n UPOPMAIL Service\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15773e1_d15774e1_d15775e1__entry__1 nlv1665702678531__table_d15773e1_d15774e1_d15775e1__entry__3\">\n 4GL UPOPMAIL\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15773e1_d15774e1_d15775e1__entry__2 nlv1665702678531__table_d15773e1_d15774e1_d15775e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">activate UPOPINSTANCE.LogonSMTP(\"server\",\"\",\"\")</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15773e1_d15774e1_d15775e1__entry__1 nlv1665702678531__table_d15773e1_d15774e1_d15775e1__entry__3\">\n 3GL UPOPMAIL\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15773e1_d15774e1_d15775e1__entry__2 nlv1665702678531__table_d15773e1_d15774e1_d15775e1__entry__3\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">LogonSMTP</code> (3GL implementation\n                        up to first call to API) </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15773e1_d15774e1_d15775e1__entry__1 nlv1665702678531__table_d15773e1_d15774e1_d15775e1__entry__3\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15773e1_d15774e1_d15775e1__entry__2 nlv1665702678531__table_d15773e1_d15774e1_d15775e1__entry__3\">\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47324e1_d47325e1_d47326e1\">Acquire API structure\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47327e1_d47328e1_d47329e1\">Establish TCP connection to <code class=\"ph codeph\">\"server\"</code>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47330e1_d47331e1_d47332e1\">Send EHLO to server\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47333e1_d47334e1_d47335e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"server\"</code> responds with a list of supported extensions\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47336e1_d47337e1_d47338e1\">Read and buffer all responses\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47339e1_d47340e1_d47341e1\">Initialize structure with buffer\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47342e1_d47343e1_d47344e1\">Initialize structure with <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_VERIFY</code> function code\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47345e1_d47346e1_d47347e1\">Call <code class=\"ph codeph\">MyModule</code> with structure parameter\n </li>\n</ol>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15776e1_d15777e1_d15778e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" colspan=\"2\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15776e1_d15777e1_d15778e1__entry__1\">\n Security Driver API\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15776e1_d15777e1_d15778e1__entry__1\">\n 3GL MyModule\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15776e1_d15777e1_d15778e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_VERIFY</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15776e1_d15777e1_d15778e1__entry__1\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"nlv1665702678531__table_d15776e1_d15777e1_d15778e1__entry__1\">\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47348e1_d47349e1_d47350e1\">Check the extension implemented in <code class=\"ph codeph\">MyModule</code> is present in buffer\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__li_d47351e1_d47352e1_d47353e1\">Return success because it is supported\n </li>\n</ol>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"nlv1665702678531__p_d132497e1_d132498e1_d132499e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">LogonSMTP</span> would continue and make further calls via the Security Driver API to <code class=\"ph codeph\">MyModule</code> using the <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_OPENMSG</code> function code. <code class=\"ph codeph\">MyModule</code> returns the message that is to be sent, and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">LogonSMTP</span> sends it over its TCP connection.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530314\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530314\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Flow of Calls to the SMTP Security Driver API Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 15, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Calls to an SMTP security driver are issued by operations on the Uniface UPOPMAIL component. These have an equivalent 3GL implementation which handles the actual call. An instance of the UPOPMAIL component can be used to open a connection and the close it, and then open a connection to another server and close it. The security context is maintained over connections so the driver receives only one call for USEC_DRVINFO . This means that when a connection is closed, the driver should return to exactly the same state it was in after the initial USEC_DRVINFO call. In this way, each new connection is created from the same starting point. The USEC_RTINFO call provides information about the current or previous connection. When a connection is being made, the driver is marked as in use depending on the USEC_VERIFY call result. Once the driver is in use, it can receive USEC_RTINFO calls. API calls are typically issued in the following order. … function may be called a number of times [] function called if the implementation supports it Table 1. Flow of API Calls to the SMTP Security Driver Calling Operation API Function Code When opening a connection: SetSecurity USEC_DRVINFO LogonSMTP (may be called implicitly by SendMail ) USEC_VERIFY LogonSMTP (may be called implicitly by SendMail ) USEC_OPENMSG … During or after a connection: GetSecurity [ USEC_RTINFO ] When closing the connection, if USEC_OPENMSG succeeded: LogoffSMTP (may be called implicitly by SendMail ) [ USEC_CLOSEMSG …] When deleting the instance: upopmail_cleanup USEC_CLOSE Interactions Between UPOPMAIL and Security API Functions The operations of the UPOPMAIL service are called using its 4GL interface. The 3GL implementations of these operations handle all TCP communication and are the callers of the generic API. The following tables show the actions and interactions between the UPOPMAIL and security driver API layers during calls to the SetSecurity and LogonSMTP operations. MyModule is an SMTP security driver implementation. It specifies its own functionality and prepares messages. Table 2. During the SetSecurity Operation Layer Call and Actions UPOPMAIL Service 4GL UPOPMAIL activate UPOPINSTANCE.SetSecurity(\"SMTP=MyModule\", \"user=andy;pass=pandy\") 3GL UPOPMAIL SetSecurity (3GL implementation) Create API structure Initialise structure with function address of MyModule Initialize structure with \"user=andy;pass=pandy\" Initialize structure with USEC_DRVINFO function code Set USE flag to Mandatory Call MyModule with structure parameter Security Driver 3GL MyModule USEC_DRVINFO Set bit flag to show USEC_OPENMSG is supported Return success Table 3. During the LogonSMTP Operation Layer Call and Actions UPOPMAIL Service 4GL UPOPMAIL activate UPOPINSTANCE.LogonSMTP(\"server\",\"\",\"\") 3GL UPOPMAIL LogonSMTP (3GL implementation up to first call to API) Acquire API structure Establish TCP connection to \"server\" Send EHLO to server \"server\" responds with a list of supported extensions Read and buffer all responses Initialize structure with buffer Initialize structure with USEC_VERIFY function code Call MyModule with structure parameter Security Driver API 3GL MyModule USEC_VERIFY Check the extension implemented in MyModule is present in buffer Return success because it is supported The LogonSMTP would continue and make further calls via the Security Driver API to MyModule using the USEC_OPENMSG function code. MyModule returns the message that is to be sent, and LogonSMTP sends it over its TCP connection. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}